         <abstract id="aspace_ef1092459ae332f596cafbaed81e840b">Manuscripts, in multiple hands, of ten business letters and legal documents concerning members of the Arundel family. The collection incldues two bonds of payment; several money orders; and two letters from R. Arundel to Sir Robert Clayton, drawing Clayton's attention to a "young lady of a considerable fortune," asking for Clayton's assistance in marriage-making for Arundel's son, and explaining what he would be willing to settle upon the couple.</abstract>
         <origination label="Creator">
            <famname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2013002164"
                     source="lcsh">
               <part localtype="agent_family">Arundel family</part>
            </famname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
